    "justification": "Five conjuncts mirroring the groove_width fixture (both sides substantive): (1)+(2) opposite signs (positive CO, negative NCO); (3)+(4) both |partial r| > 0.1 above noise; (5) Steiger Z p < 0.01 confirms the CO vs NCO difference is significant. wrapping_energy is a Layer-2 nucleosome track; the pattern matches groove_width with somewhat smaller magnitudes.",
    "failure_mode": "If either partial r changed sign or both magnitudes dropped below 0.1, or if Steiger p > 0.01, the sign-flip claim for wrapping_energy fails. Current margin |r_NCO| = 0.125 above the 0.1 floor is the smallest, making NCO magnitude the load-bearing conjunct."
  },
  "conclusion": {
    "assertion": "After GC residualization, mean wrapping energy at 1 Mb autosomal resolution has a positive partial Spearman correlation with crossover rate (+0.166) and an opposite-signed correlation with non-crossover rate (-0.125); the difference is significant by Steiger's Z. Lower-energy (more-favorable) nucleosomal wrapping promotes non-crossover resolution while disfavoring crossover resolution — consistent with a mechanical preference for open DNA during strand invasion.",
